me.taylorkelly.mywarp.warp

Class EventWarpManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.taylorkelly.mywarp.warp.AbstractWarpManager
      • me.taylorkelly.mywarp.warp.EventWarpManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WarpManager

    public class EventWarpManager
extends AbstractWarpManager
    Provides an event-framework for the Warps managed by it. Warps can fire WarpEvents through this manager and the manager itself will fire WarpAdditionEvents and WarpRemovalEvents when Warps are added to or removed from it. Handlers can listen to these events by registering themselves at this manager and providing the appropriate handler methods annotated by Subscribe annotations.

    This manager fires all events in the thread it runs. Events cannot be expected to be threadsafe and it lies in the responsibility of the handler to manage further thread-safety if required.

    See Also:
    EventBus
